Build a web app called "IE Report Maker" for TCET.

---

## OVERVIEW

User fills in metadata on the website UI.
User pastes their report content section by section.
App formats everything and exports a professional multi-page PDF.

NO AI generation. NO Claude API. Pure formatting + PDF export only.

---

## TECH STACK

- React (Vite) + plain CSS
- html2pdf.js for PDF export
- No backend, no API calls, no auth

---

## PDF SPECIFICATIONS (enforce strictly)

Font: Times New Roman
Font Size: 12pt
Alignment: Justified
Line Spacing: 1.15
Margin: 2.54cm all sides (Normal)
Orientation: Portrait
Page size: A4

---

## PAGE 1 — COVER PAGE

### HEADER (copy exactly from reference image)

Three-column layout inside the header:

LEFT COLUMN:
- Square logo block with orange/red border
- Text inside: "tcet" (small), "ES&H" (large block letters), "ENGINEERS"
- Use an <img> tag if logo image is provided, else replicate as styled HTML div

CENTER COLUMN (centered text):
- Line 1: "TCET" — bold, large (~16pt)
- Line 2: "DEPARTMENT OF ENGINEERING SCIENCES AND HUMANITIES" — bold, orange/amber color (#E07B00 approx), ~11pt
- Line 3: "Choice Based Credit Grading Scheme with Holistic and Multidisciplinary Education" — regular, ~9pt
- Line 4: "Under Autonomy - CBCGS-HME 2023" — regular, ~9pt
- Line 5: "University of Mumbai" — bold, ~11pt

RIGHT COLUMN:
- Circular TCET logo (use <img> or styled placeholder circle with "tcet Est.2001")

Below the three-column header:
- Full-width horizontal rule (1px solid black)
- Another thinner rule just below it (double line effect)

---

### COVER PAGE BODY (all centered, Times New Roman)

Gap after header (~60px)

[PROJECT TITLE]
- Font: Times New Roman, Bold, 20pt
- Centered
- User-editable field: "Title of Project"
- Allow 2 lines if long

Gap (~40px)

[GROUP LINE]
- "By Group No. ___ Comp ___"
- Bold, 14pt, centered
- Two input fields: Group Number + Division/Comp letter

Gap (~30px)

[STUDENTS TABLE]
- Bordered table, 2 columns × up to 10 rows
- Each cell: Roll No. + Student Name (bold, ~13pt)
- Example: "23. Pranay Chavan | 28. Saquib Chougle"
- User inputs: up to 10 students (Roll No + Name per student)
- Render only filled rows in PDF

Gap (~40px)

[SUBMISSION BLOCK — centered, all bold]
- "An Innovative Examination (IE) Report" — bold, 12pt
- "Submitted for" — bold, 12pt
- "The subject of" — bold, 12pt
- Subject Name — bold, 18pt (e.g. "Engineering Mechanics (EM)")
- "Under the guidance of" — bold, 12pt
- Faculty Name — bold, 22pt (e.g. "Mr. Pawan Tiwari")

Gap to bottom

[PAGE NUMBER]
- Centered at bottom: "1"

---

## PAGE 2 ONWARDS — CONTENT PAGES

### HEADER (same on every page including page 1)

Exact same three-column TCET header as Page 1.
Followed by double horizontal rule.
No cover page body — just header then content flows below.

### CONTENT

User pastes text for each section into labeled textareas on the website.
Sections appear in order from page 2, one after another with page breaks handled automatically by html2pdf.

Sections (in this exact order):
1. Title of Project        ← auto-pulled from cover field, render as section heading only
2. Theoretical Background  ← user textarea
3. Introduction            ← user textarea
4. Literature Survey       ← user textarea
5. Methodology Used / Current Trends ← user textarea
6. Future Scope            ← user textarea (optional — skip section entirely if empty)
7. Conclusion              ← user textarea
8. Acknowledgement         ← user textarea
9. References              ← user textarea (split by newline → render as numbered <ol>)

### SECTION FORMATTING

Section heading:
- Times New Roman, 12pt, Bold, Underlined, Left-aligned
- Example: "2. Theoretical Background"

Section body:
- Times New Roman, 12pt, Justified, line-height 1.15
- 14px margin below each section

### FOOTER (pages 2 onwards only, not on cover page)

Left: "Student's Signature: ___________"
Right: "Teacher's Signature: ___________"
Center: page number (starting at 2)
Font: 10pt, Times New Roman

---

## WEBSITE UI LAYOUT

Two-panel layout. Left panel = cover fields. Right panel = content sections.

### LEFT PANEL — Cover Page Fields

Label + input for each:
- Title of Project (text input, full width)
- Group Number (short input)
- Division / Comp (short input, e.g. "A", "B")
- Subject Name (text input)
- Subject Code (short input, optional)
- Faculty Name (text input)
- Date of Submission (date picker or text input)

Students section (up to 10 rows):
- Repeating row: [Roll No input] [Student Name input] [+ Add Row button]
- Minimum 1 row shown by default, max 10
- Show "Add Student" button below rows

### RIGHT PANEL — Report Content Sections

Labeled textarea for each of the 9 sections:
- Label shows section number + name
- Placeholder: "Paste your content here..."
- Min height: 120px, resizable vertically
- Future Scope label includes "(optional)"

### BOTTOM BAR

Full-width navy button: "Download PDF"
On click:
- Validate: Title and at least 1 student name must be filled
- If invalid: show inline red error message, do not generate
- If valid: generate and download PDF

Filename: Title_GroupNo_IEReport.pdf (spaces replaced with underscores)

---

## COLLEGE HEADER CONFIG FILE

Create src/config/collegeHeader.js:

export const collegeHeader = {
  department: "Department of Engineering Sciences and Humanities",
  departmentColor: "#E07B00",
  line3: "Choice Based Credit Grading Scheme with Holistic and Multidisciplinary Education",
  line4: "Under Autonomy - CBCGS-HME 2023",
  university: "University of Mumbai",
  logoLeftImage: null,       // path to left square logo image
  logoRightImage: null,      // path to right circular logo image
  logoLeftText: "ES&H",      // fallback if no image
  logoRightText: "tcet",     // fallback if no image
  accentColor: "#E07B00",
}

PDF header reads ONLY from this object. To switch colleges: update only this file.

---

## FOLDER STRUCTURE

ie-report-maker/
├── index.html
├── public/
│   ├── logo-left.png        ← place TCET square logo here
│   └── logo-right.png       ← place TCET circular logo here
├── src/
│   ├── main.jsx
│   ├── App.jsx
│   ├── config/
│   │   └── collegeHeader.js
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── CoverFields.jsx        ← left panel inputs
│   │   ├── ContentFields.jsx      ← right panel textareas
│   │   └── PDFExporter.jsx        ← builds HTML string → html2pdf → download
│   └── styles/
│       └── app.css

---

## STEP BY STEP BUILD ORDER

Step 1:
Scaffold Vite + React project.
Install only: html2pdf.js
Run: npm create vite@latest ie-report-maker -- --template react
Then: cd ie-report-maker && npm install html2pdf.js

Step 2:
Create src/config/collegeHeader.js with the object above.

Step 3:
Build CoverFields.jsx
- Controlled state for all cover fields
- Dynamic student rows (add/remove)
- Expose all values via onChange prop or lift state to App.jsx

Step 4:
Build ContentFields.jsx
- 9 labeled textareas with section names
- Expose all values via onChange prop or lift state to App.jsx

Step 5:
Build PDFExporter.jsx

Function: buildPDFHTML(coverData, contentData, headerConfig)
Returns a full HTML string structured as:

<!-- ========== PAGE 1: COVER ========== -->
<div class="page cover-page">
  [HEADER HTML]        ← three-column layout from collegeHeader.js
  [DOUBLE RULE]
  [COVER BODY]         ← title, group, students table, submission block
  [PAGE NUMBER: 1]
</div>

<!-- ========== PAGE BREAK ========== -->
<div style="page-break-before: always;"></div>

<!-- ========== PAGES 2+: CONTENT ========== -->
<div class="page content-page">
  [HEADER HTML]        ← same header repeated
  [DOUBLE RULE]
  [SECTIONS]           ← loop through 9 sections, skip if empty
  [FOOTER]             ← signatures + page number
</div>

html2pdf options:
{
  margin: [25.4, 25.4, 25.4, 25.4],
  filename: generated_filename,
  image: { type: 'jpeg', quality: 1 },
  html2canvas: { scale: 2, useCORS: true },
  jsPDF: { unit: 'mm', format: 'a4', orientation: 'portrait' }
}

Global CSS inside the HTML string (injected as <style>):
body {
  font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;
  font-size: 12pt;
  line-height: 1.15;
  color: #000;
}
.section-heading {
  font-weight: bold;
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-align: left;
  margin-top: 18px;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}
p, li {
  text-align: justify;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.cover-title {
  font-size: 20pt;
  font-weight: bold;
  text-align: center;
}
.students-table {
  border-collapse: collapse;
  width: 70%;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
.students-table td {
  border: 1.5px solid #000;
  padding: 6px 14px;
  font-weight: bold;
  font-size: 13pt;
}
.page-number {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 11pt;
  margin-top: 20px;
}
.footer {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  font-size: 10pt;
  margin-top: 30px;
  border-top: 0.5px solid #000;
  padding-top: 6px;
}

Step 6:
Wire everything in App.jsx
- State: coverData object + contentData object
- Pass setters to CoverFields and ContentFields
- Download button calls PDFExporter with both data objects + collegeHeader

Step 7:
Style app.css
- Background: #f5f5f5
- Two-column layout: left 380px fixed, right fills remaining
- Each panel scrollable independently
- Textarea cards: white bg, 1px border #ddd, border-radius 6px, padding 12px
- Labels: 13px, #555, font-weight 500
- Download button: background #1a3a6b, color white, padding 14px, full width, font-size 15px
- Add student button: outlined, small, navy border
- Error message: red, 13px, shown below download button

---

## STRICT RULES

1. Never hardcode college name, department, or logo anywhere except collegeHeader.js
2. Future Scope: skip section heading AND body if textarea is empty
3. References: split textarea by newline → render as <ol><li> per line
4. PDF title on page 2 is a heading only (no body text under it, just the section label)
5. Students table: render only rows where name is not empty
6. Validate before PDF generation: block if Title is empty OR zero students entered
7. Logo images: load from /public/ folder using relative path; if null in config, render styled HTML placeholder div instead
8. Page numbers: page 1 shows "1" centered at bottom of cover; pages 2+ show number in footer center
9. The header HTML block must be identical on every page — built from one shared function renderHeader(config)
10. Do not use any CSS framework — plain CSS only



